title: Bondi lifeguard pictured running barefoot in viral photo recalls night of terror attack | ABC NEWS
description: Much of Jackson Doolan's memory from December 14 is a blur, but there is one moment that remains crystal clear.   The Bondi lifeguard was one of the first people on the scene after two gunmen began to shoot at the Chanukah by the Sea Jewish celebration.   In his first television interview since the tragedy, Mr Doolan spoke with the ABC about the shock and chaos that unfolded.   Amidst the confusion, he remembers treating 14-year-old Chaya, who had been shot in the leg.   #Sydney #Bondi #ABCNewsNSW  ABC NEWS provides around the clock coverage of news events as they break in Australia and abroad. title: More than 1,000 cane toads caught in one night at Darwin botanic gardens | ABC NEWS
description: Cane toads are usually the last thing you want to see outside, but some Territorians turn out in droves to hunt them down.  The first toad bust in over ten years at Darwin's botanical gardens was a huge, rainy success, capturing more than a thousand toads in just a few hours. By Tilda Colling for ABC News Northern Territory. title: Aussie dollar hits 15-month high on rising odds of RBA rate hike | Finance Report | ABC NEWS
description: The likelihood of an interest rate hike by the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) has increased following an unexpected decline in Australia's unemployment rate. This led the Australian dollar to jump to its highest level since October 2024.  The ASX, Wall Street and other share markets recovered after tensions between Europe and Donald Trump, over the fate of Greenland, appeared to have cooled down. Finance presenter David Chau explains.  Subscribe: http://ab.co/1svxLVE  ABC NEWS provides around the clock coverage of news events as they break in Australia and abroad. title: Young girl among missing campers at New Zealand's Mount Maunganui after landslide | ABC NEWS
description: A desperate search for survivors is underway in New Zealand at a Bay of Plenty camp ground. Several people are missing, including a young girl, after a landslide hit a holiday park at Mount Maunganui on the north island. Earlier, two people were killed in another landslip which destroyed a house in Welcome Bay. title: Bondi attack victims remembered on National Day of Mourning | ABC NEWS
description: Australians across the country have come together to mourn the victims of the Bondi attack. In Sydney, flags were flown at half-mast on the Harbour Bridge, and the atmosphere at the Bondi Pavilion was quiet and respectful as mourners visited a small memorial decorated with pebbles. Prime Minister Anthony Albanese addressed the public outside Parliament House in Canberra before going to the evening ceremony at the Opera House in Sydney. title: Some Adelaide University students unable to enrol in courses since merger | ABC NEWS
description: The Adelaide University merger is resulting in students having difficulties with their enrolments and study plans.  Frustrated students say there has been limited communication and support from the university.  Adelaide University's vice-chancellor says there are "lumps and bumps" to be ironed out but staff are available to help at hubs on campus this week.
